# pychron ‚è±Ô∏è

**pychron** is a simple command-line tool that shows the execution time of your Python scripts in real time.

It prints the **elapsed time while the script is running**, and shows a clean **summary** when the script finishes.

---

## ‚ú® Features

- ‚úÖ Shows elapsed time in real time (live timer)
- ‚úÖ Does not break or hide your script output (`stdout`)
- ‚úÖ Prints **start time**, **finish time**, and **total time**
- ‚úÖ Colorful and terminal-friendly ANSI output
- ‚úÖ Very lightweight and easy to use

---

## üì¶ Installation

Install using pip:

```bash
pip3.12 install pychron
```

```bash

pychron main.py


```
